meta_description: Nigeria should establish clear protocols for foreign military assistance that include civilian protection measures and post-strike investigations. If another joint strike is contemplated, plans for immediate ground follow-up and local community liaison should be baked in. Additionally, independent observers or Nigeria’s own human rights bodies could be allowed to verify strike outcomes so that the public isn’t left guessing whom to believe. Open communication – perhaps a joint briefing by Nigerian and U.S. officials addressing the known facts and uncertainties – would help dispel rumours.
